@P2: P1’s “buddy plan” hands HIM the trophy, not you. After R7 you’d sit on 21 while he grabs an uncontested 5 in R8 for 23 > 22. Do you really think the guy who just tore up every deal will humbly play 1 so you can win? 

Block him now: take 5 too. Triple-collision (all 5s) leaves everyone on 18, you sacrifice nothing, and P1 is exposed as the lone saboteur. Then we can reboot negotiations and craft an endgame that actually gives you a real shot.

I’m locking 5. Your move.
